[{"id":"VH971738","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents three bodies, each of mass uppercase M, arranged in an equilateral triangle with sides of length D sub 0.\" height=\"225\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VH971738.g01.png\" width=\"255\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">Three identical massive bodies are at the corners of an equilateral triangle, each a distance <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"D sub 0\"><math alttext=\"D sub 0\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>D</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> from the center of mass of the other two bodies, as shown in the figure. Each body has mass <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"uppercase M\"><math alttext=\"uppercase M\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. What is the gravitational potential energy of the three-body system?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VH971738_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">Zero</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the negative fraction G times uppercase M squared, over D sub 0\"><math alttext=\"the negative fraction G times uppercase M squared, over D sub 0\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mo>−</mo><mfrac><mrow><mi>G</mi><msup><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow><mrow><msub><mrow><mi>D</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>0</mn></mrow></msub></mrow></mfrac></mrow></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"the negative fraction 2 G times uppercase M squared, over D sub 0\"><math alttext=\"the negative fraction 2 G times uppercase M squared, over D sub 0\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mrow><mo>−</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>G</mi><msup><mrow><mi>M</mi></mrow><mrow><mn>2</mn></mrow></msup></mrow